narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: An enjoyable, if somewhat idiosyncratic, survey of French science and thinkers of the past. Readings can be a bit obtuse, but are manageable. Professor Reilly made class fly by (even on Friday afternoons) and is very helpful. Workload includes two class presentations, a book review, and a final project.
Dont take it unless you are somehow actually interested in the subject. There was not much work though.

I thought this course was rather good. Reilly has cobbled together a syllabus that covers a lot of different interesting topics. He does not assign busywork; I enjoyed the work that I did for this class.
This is a great class! You do have to tackle some complicated readings at times, but it is well worth it.
